```julia
function clean_column(col)
    return Symbol(lowercase(replace(col, r"[^a-zA-Z]" => "")), "_")
end
```
This function takes a `String` or `SubString` and returns a `Symbol` with the specified cleaning applied. It first removes all non-alphanumeric characters using `replace` with a custom regex that matches everything except letters (`a-zA-Z`), then lowercases the string, and finally converts it to a `Symbol` with underscores.
